STRICTLY FOLLOW:

HTML - only for structure
CSS - only for decoration
Javascript - for functions

->
document.querySelector("button").classList;
 this will provide all the classes available with buttons
document.querySelector("button").classList.add("invisible"); -
this will add invisible class with button

->
we can add,remove and toggle a class name


->innerHTML; and textContent; have differences
1.innerHTML, we can target even the style of text, whether
em or i
2.textContent, we can only target what the text is and not the
style.

-><a> by using this tag we learnt the property of attributes
1.document.querySelector("a").attributes();
2.document.querySelector("a").getAttribute("href");
3.document.querySelector("a").setAttribute("href",website URL);
